- If the text is "How many people does Honda employ in the U.S.?", the correct label is 'numeric' because the answer would be a number, even though 'people' (humans) are discussed.
- If the text is "What Batman character tools around on a Batcycle?", the correct label is 'human' because the answer expected is a person or character, even though 'Batcycle' (an entity) is mentioned.

Your output should be only the one-word category name—no extra formatting, punctuation, explanations, or commentary. Always ensure your choice reflects the kind of entity the answer to the input will be, using the definitions above.
