- Requests to delete, remove, or cancel meetings/events/appointments are calendar_remove—even if phrasing is ambiguous or indirect, as in "find remainder and delete."
- List-related actions are: lists_createoradd (for adding/creating lists or items), lists_query (to check contents), lists_remove (removing items or lists). If there is ambiguity between list removal and calendar event removal (such as "delete remainder"), always prefer calendar_remove if there is any real-world evidence or typical usage supporting it.
- Alarm-related actions (setting, checking) use alarm_set or alarm_query.
